arget=\"_blank\">https://www.facebook.com/105332320817333/posts/357611162256113/</a><br />\n<br />\n【Concerns raised about Glen Eira City Council Candidate&rsquo;s links to the Chinese Communist Party (CCP) associated group】<br />\n<br />\nArticle by Alex Chung (<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/alex.c.chung.1\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2Falex.c.chung.1&d=lMjb5htdGhqouCxjtFETmTv6TERBNTdTd%2BiGQaA%2FLRg%3D&h=481b76bd\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.facebook.com/alex.c.chung.1</a>), summary by VHKTSA editorial team<br />\n<br />\nlink to full article: <a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1yLMGTbyeCeCu6ugdUE92LvfM5KE6HpK4h-NiJnDxOMQ/edit?usp=sharing\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.google.com%2Fdocument%2Fd%2F1yLMGTbyeCeCu6ugdUE92LvfM5KE6HpK4h-NiJnDxOMQ%2Fedit%3Fusp%3Dsharing&d=lMjb5htdGhqouCxjtFETmTv6TERBNTdTd%2BiGQaA%2FLRg%3D&h=235824f4\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://docs.google.com/document/d/1yLMGTbyeCeCu6ugdUE92LvfM5KE6HpK4h-NiJnDxOMQ/edit?usp=sharing</a><br />\n<br />\nSummary:<br />\nLi Zhang (Li Zhang for Tucker Ward), president of the Chinese Communist Party-associated Chinese Community Council of Australia, Victoria Branch (CCCAV) is running for a Tucker Ward seat on the Glen Eira City Council.<br />\n<br />\nMs Zhang is also the current CEO of the Australian-China Economic Trade and Investment Expo (ACETIE), headed by former Liberal Trade Minister Andrew Robb, who took an $880,000 job with the Chinese owned company that controversially secured a 99-year lease for the Port of Darwin.<br />\n<br />\nMs Zhang also worked for then Parliamentary Secretary for Multicultural Affairs, Hong Lim.  Mr Lim sits on the advisory council of the CCCAV and another CCP-linked organisation known as the Australian Council for the Promotion of Peaceful Reunification of China (ACPPRC).<br />\n<br />\nProfessor Clive Hamilton has characterised both the CCCAV and ACPPRC as &lsquo;United Front&rsquo; organisations designed to influence and recruit members of the Chinese diaspora to proliferate CCP interests in Australia and abroad.<br />\n<br />\nSerious concerns have been raised about Li Zhang&rsquo;s failure to disclose these political associations on her English candidate statement.  In a YouTube video, which has now been taken down, Ms Zhang tells the viewer about her role in the Victorian Parliament under Hong Lim.  This, however, is not disclosed to her English or other language speaking constituents, of which 63.9% speak English at home only.<br />\n<br />\nClive Hamilton: Hidden Hand -  How the Chinese Communist Party is Reshaping the World<br />\n#HongLim<br />\nVote 1 Joanne Beilby for Glen Eira<br />\nCr Jim Magee Glen Eira Council  Election  October 2020<br />\n<br />\n---------------------------------<br />\n<br />\nFacebook: <a href=\"http://fb.com/vhktsa\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=http%3A%2F%2Ffb.com%2Fvhktsa&d=lMjb5htdGhqouCxjtFETmTv6TERBNTdTd%2BiGQaA%2FLRg%3D&h=5a4eb5e6\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">fb.com/vhktsa</a><br />\nInstagram: @vhktsa<br />\nTelegram: @vhktsa<br />\nEmail: 2020vhktsa@gmail.com"},{"pid":"78a1f8dabf6fa6ee8e0c323350f6fb596d541662","tid":2233814,"uid":246262,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"52598af2ccca2d49a9edaf33154a853322f0a3c7","tid":2233814,"uid":5218,"like":16,"dislike":1,"score":15,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2020-10-07T12:06:21.000Z","msg":"趁而家滅共就應該褫奪佢個公民身份。"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-10-07T12:08:41.000Z","msg":"人哋仲開開心心選緊<img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/haha.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"4e442ebaaf4cc4034a20d4bc1cc0816cb0af17d1","tid":2233814,"uid":232466,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-10-07T12:10:44.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/no.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"e170bea3cf789c73c33ab24b06036a0000404790","tid":2233814,"uid":232466,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-10-07T12:10